<span id="freeTextContainer2691964931979129119"><strong>Absolutely amazing!</strong><br/><br/>I liked especially the vivid descriptions of Canton, its people and life during that time in history. The narrative is richly and eloquently layered and poignantly reveals the cultural, moral, philosophical, historical, political and economic aspects and appalling realities of opium trade and wars. Ibis trilogy is indispensable reading to understand the history of China and India.</span>

